rounds.event: Georgian capital Tbilisi falls to the invading Russian forces after heavy fighting and the Russians declare the Georgian Soviet Socialist Republic.

rounds.event: As part of British air raid precautions, the first of 2.5 million Anderson shelters is constructed in a garden in Islington, north London.
Marie-Adélaïde, the eldest of six daughters of Guillaume IV, becomes the first reigning Grand Duchess of Luxembourg.
deaths: William IV, Grand Duke of Luxembourg

rounds.event: People Power Revolution: President of the Philippines Ferdinand Marcos flees the nation after 20 years of rule; Corazon Aquino becomes the Philippines' first female president.

Jameela Jamil, English actress and presenter

rounds.event: Disbandment of the Warsaw Pact at a meeting of its members in Budapest.
